        <marc:datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
            <marc:subfield code="a">A copy of the Tawḍīḥ, which is a commentary on another work by al-Maḥbūbī called Tanqīḥ al-uṣūl; three other, shorter works are also included: on metaphor, on abbrogated verses and one poem in Persian.</marc:subfield>
        </marc:datafield>
        <marc:datafield tag="546" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
            <marc:subfield code="a">Arabic with some Persian.</marc:subfield>
        </marc:datafield>
        <marc:datafield tag="505" ind1="0" ind2=" ">
            <marc:subfield code="a">1. f. 1v-4r: Farāʼid al-fawāʼid li-taḥqīq maʻānī al-istiʻārah -- 2. f. 4v-31v:  Kitāb al-nāsikh wa-al-mansūkh -- 3. f. 32r-33v : Risālah-i Mullā Zāhirī -- 4. f. 36v-336v: al-Tawḍīḥ -- 5. f. 337v-338v: [Notes]</marc:subfield>
        </marc:datafield>
        <marc:datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
            <marc:subfield code="a">Foliation: Modern foliation in pencil added, upper left recto; catchwords every verso, lower left.</marc:subfield>
        </marc:datafield>
        <marc:datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
            <marc:subfield code="a">Layout: Written in 15-19 long lines; partially border-ruled.</marc:subfield>
        </marc:datafield>
        <marc:datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
            <marc:subfield code="a">Script: Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink, pointed.</marc:subfield>
        </marc:datafield>
        <marc:datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
            <marc:subfield code="a">Decoration: Rubrications in red.</marc:subfield>
        </marc:datafield>
        <marc:datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
            <marc:subfield code="a">Binding: Lacquered boards with floral center and text in the border; insides are gold floral designs on a black ground.</marc:subfield>
        </marc:datafield>
        <marc:datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
            <marc:subfield code="a">Origin: Long work is dated Ramadan 1241 A.H. (1826 CE) (f. 336v) and each shorter work is dated 1242 A.H. (1827 CE).</marc:subfield>
        </marc:datafield>
        <marc:datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
            <marc:subfield code="a">Description from auction catalog, number 362, tipped in before front flyleaf; note in pencil on clipping, &quot;Carnegie Cat 334, June 1973&quot;.</marc:subfield>
